message.content:
cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with image synthesis and style transfer.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as the paper focuses on generating artistic glyph images.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes a novel model for automatic generation of artistic glyph images.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed model uses two encoders and two decoders to disentangle content and style representations and generate glyph shape and texture images.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the paper deals with generating stylized glyph images from a large-scale dataset of Chinese glyph images in various shape and texture styles.
